title: Baked Sausage Gigantes Plaki with Garlic Parsley Ciabatta
description: Gigantes plaki are a typical Greek mezze, consisting of beans that are soaked before being slow cooked in a chunky tomato sauce. When made with butter beans, locals will also refer to this dish as "Herakles' beans", referring to the mythological hero Herakles (Hercules) who was known for his superhuman strength.
