== Gigantes Plaki ==

Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large, wide-bottomed ovenproof pan on 
medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @British Pork and Oregano Sausage Meat{225%g} and fry until 
browned, ~{5-6%mins}.

Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks, then drain and discard any excess 
fat.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. It's 
> cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

In the meantime, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{3}(peeled and grated) (or 
use a #garlic press{}). Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(halved, peeled and 
chopped) into small pieces.

Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1%bunch}(roughly chopped, stalks and all). 
Drain and rinse the @butter beans{1%carton} in a #sieve{}. Cut the 
@medium tomatoes{2}(cut into medium chunks) into medium chunks.

Once the sausage meat is cooked, transfer to a #plate{} lined with kitchen 
paper. Wipe out the pan.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} and a knob of @?butter{} in the (now empty) pan 
on medium heat.

Once hot, add the onion, season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{} and fry, 
stirring occasionally, until golden and softened, ~{8-10%mins}. Add the tomato 
chunks and half the garlic and fry for ~{1-2%mins} more.

Stir in the cooked sausage meat, @tomato passata{1%carton}, 
@red wine stock paste{28%g}, butter beans, @dried oregano{1%sachet}, 
@dried thyme{1%sachet}, @sugar{1%tsp} and @water{100%ml} for the sauce. Bring 
up to the boil, then lower to a simmer.

> See pantry for sugar and water amounts.

Bake on the middle shelf of your oven for ~{10-15%mins}.

== Garlic Parsley Ciabatta ==

While your gigantes plaki are in the oven, halve the @ciabatta{1} and lay onto 
a medium #baking tray{}, cut-side up. Drizzle with the @olive oil{1%tbsp} for 
the garlic bread, spread over the remaining garlic and sprinkle over half the 
parsley.

> See pantry for amount of olive oil.

When there are ~{5%mins} left, bake the garlic bread on the bottom shelf of 
your oven until golden, ~{4-5%mins}.

== To Serve ==

When your gigantes plaki are ready, taste and season with salt and pepper if 
needed.

Share the gigantes plaki between your #serving bowls{}. Sprinkle over the 
remaining parsley.

Serve the herby garlic ciabatta alongside. Enjoy!